dict.string: stiffness of links between the Solid and the Fiber. stiffness[0] is the link between the central point of the Solid and the focus-end of the Fiberstiffness[1] is the link between a secondary point of the Solid and an intermediate point of the Fiber. This holds the Fiber in direction.
designates which end of the fiber is towards the center
rate at which a new fiber is created at an unoccupied site (known as nucleate)
name of Fiber that make up the Aster (know as nucleate[1])
specifications for initial fibers (also known as nucleate[2])
